inn1.comm: lands outside the off stump and it leaves him, late swing, it's a no-ball as well
this was a touch shorter and he swiveled and pulled it to the on side, mistimed
cuts back in and he clips it down to square leg
drifts towards the pads and he tucks this one away to fine leg
a touch shorter and he safely leaves it alone
stays behind the line and defends back to the bowler
this one swings back in sharply, tucks inwards and traps him on the pads outside the line of the off stump
close to being called a wide, lands outside the off stump and Wade watchfully leaves it alone
outside edge this time, full and wide outside the off stump, reaches out and the edge drops well short of second slip and races to third man
Umar Akmal has dropped it! Junaid squared him up on the off stump and he got a leading edge to point, Umar was behind it but couldn't hang on as he fell forward

well Umar Akmal needn't beat himself up for that drop! Soon after being let off, Wade chases a full and wide delivery outside off and drags it to his stumps, not exactly a wicket-taking delivery though, the shot didn't come off right
drifts down the leg side and wide called
gets beside the line and he pushes it to the off side
was that really a wide down the leg side? Thought I heard a sound, bat hitting pad probably as he tried to flick it
full and wide outside off and he drives towards mid-off
tucks it away off his thighs to the leg side
fuller delivery and Clarke gets in front of the stumps and defends with soft hands
he has overstepped again, left alone, two front foot no-balls already from a Pakistan left-armer - Wasim Akram-esque
fails to out away the free hit, he makes room and forces it down to mid-on
this was too full and straight on the pads, Clarke gets off the mark with a stylish flick wide of midwicket and mid-on
thats more the line Tanvir should be bowling, this left Clarke just over the off stump, cramped him up for room
struggling with the extras here, this was outside the off stump and he safely left it alone, too wide
drifts on the body and he clips it to square leg
fractionally short of a length outside off and he leaves it alone
beats him! This was angled across Clarke who was sucked in to the off drive, fuller delivery, nearly took the edge
yet another wide, down the leg side this time, both seamers struggling a bit
that was spanked past the covers, half volley wide outside the off stump and Clarke ensured he was well across to meet the pitch of the ball, mid-off dived in vain

appeal for an lbw and he's been given not out, Misbah is not reviewing it and wisely so, it landed on the off stump and didn't move away, Clarke was forward and he was trapped on the front pad, that looked like clearing the stumps
slightly short and he punches it to the off side
drifts on the body and he tucks it down to fine leg
well fielded on the boundary, tucked off the pads and midwicket (Shafiq) gives chase and times his dive well at the boundary to pull it back
keeps it nice and straight and he gets behind the line and knocks it back to the bowler
behind the line and he gets an inside edge to the on side
stays beside the line and knocks it to the off side
nips back in and he stays behind the line and knocks it to the off side
keeps it straight on the stumps and he defends down the track
defensive push through the on side, timed well enough to beat mid-on and the fielder does well to give chase
delivers from slightly wide of the crease, keeps it straight and Warner knocks it back to the bowler
oh well he induces another inside edge, luckily for Warner he drags it onto his boot
good length outside the off stump and he stays back and defends
comes from wide of the crease again and Warner steers it straight to Umar Akmal at point
nudged away off the pads to the on side, and Warner is still not off the mark
tries to flick and he misses it, clipped off the pads to the on side, still runs for Warner
comes round the wicket, angles it in middle and leg and he clips it to mid-on
delivers from wide of the crease and lands it full, luckily for him the drive went straight to mid-on
slower ball outside off and on a good length, steers it down to point
Tanvir bowls the bouncer, Clarke ducks under that one
it was a fraction too short, Clarke read the length well and swiveled and clubbed it just over midwicket's reach, safe enough
bowls it flat and on a good length, Warner stabs at it and nearly carries all the way to cover
hint of turn, stays back and defends
quicker and skids through, he steers it to point
off the mark finally! Stops before delivery but strays on the pads, clipped wide of midwicket
slower through the air and worked straight to midwicket
chips down the track and checks his shot, clips it to short fine leg
angles it inwards and he stays beside the line and steers it to the off side
angles it inwards again and Warner stays right behind the line to defend
bit too straight, Warner shuffles and clips it in front of his hips and exploited the big gap on the leg side, Ajmal gives chase but can't cut it off, this outfield is much quicker than Sharjah's
close call for Warner as he fishes outside off and nearly edges to Kamran
stays beside the line and taps it to cover, tells his partner to wait
brings it back in to the left-hander and he slices it down to point
slower through the air and clipped own to mid-on
took the risk of leaving that one, the slider just sneaks past the off stump
makes a bit of room and he punches it down to extra cover, this one didn't turn
flighted on off and he gets forward to defends
flatter delivery and tucks off the pads to square leg
tossed up on middle and leg and he drives wide of silly mid-on
Rehman tosses it up on the off stump and he clips it down to deep midwicket
flatter delivery and he clips it towards midwicket
sharp turn and neat bounce too! Warner tried to flick it to the leg side and and failed to make contact
gets right behind it and defends
straighter delivery and he gets back and defends
slight turn and he knocks it to the on side
tossed up on middle and leg and worked down to deep midwicket
quicker delivery and he comes forward and pushes it down the pitch
flatter and shorter and he rocks back and slices it to cover
tossed up slowly and Clarke uses his feet and works it to wide long-on
rocks back and slaps that one straight to extra cover and there's a misfield
comes down the track and he works it down to long-on
slower through the air and he works it off his pads down to square leg
stays back and punches it down to long-on
flatter delivery and pushed through the line to long-off
stays back and clips it down to mid-on
slower through the air and he works it straight to midwicket
Hafeez drifts towards middle and Clarke uses his feet and clips it round the corner to fine leg
stays back and punches it with the turn to cover
goes back at the crease and he clips it to midwicket
stays back at the crease and he punches it back to the bowler
pushes it with the spin to long-on
clips it against the spin to midwicket
warner was forward and the ball skidded through and nearly took the edge, Kamran was quite confident but umpire Llong wasn't so sure
stays back and clips it to the on side
tossed up on the off stump and he defends
goes back and clips it just wide of midwicket
tossed up full outside the off stump and he drives him through the line to long-off and these two have brought up the 50 stand
tossed up and driven down the ground to long-on
comes round the wicket, gets across and taps it wide of point
tossed up on the pads and worked away down to square leg
tossed up on middle and leg and he pushes it to mid-on
flatter delivery and he stays back and punches it to point
cuts straight to point
goes back and punches to cover
tossed up ball on the off stump. Clarke comes forward in defense
how close was Clarke to getting dismissed? He rocks back and looks to cut it and gets an inside edge that sails over the stumps
defends it to the leg side
fuller ball outside the off stump. Clarke defends it to the off side
comes forward and pushes it to long-on for a single
fuller ball on the leg stump. Warner turns it to deep square-leg for a single
comes forward and defends it to the leg side
drives it off the backfoot to cover
finally the patience snaps! The slog comes into play now and gets a top edge and it just sails over mid-on
turns it to square-leg for a single
fuller ball outside the off stump. Clarke comes forward and defends it back onto the pitch
pads it away to the off side
turn there as Warner looks to turn it away but gets an inside edge onto the pads
short ball outside the off stump. Warner rocks back and smashes one past covers for a boundary
comes forward and defends it to the leg side
on the leg stump. Warner turns it to deep square-leg for a single
fuller ball on the leg stump. Clarke looks to push it to the leg side and gets an inside edge to fine-leg for a couple
comes forward and drives it to mid-on
straighter ball that Warner manages to defend to the off side
flighted ball outside the off stump. Warner comes forward and defends it to the off side
pushes it to midwicket. Clarke doesn't want to take a single off a misfield
comes forward and drives it to cover

and the long, long vigil comes to an end! Pitching on the leg and middle, hitting on the pad and struck low on the pads. Ticks all the boxes required to dole out an LBW decision. Ajmal is ecstatic. Warner is asked,by his captain, if he wants to use the referral, but he refuses it
turns it to square-leg to get off the mark
tossed up outside off and driven down the ground to long-off
slow through the air and clipped straight to midwicket
chips down the track and driven just wide of the bowler and down to long-on
driven back to the bowler
gets forward and drills it down the ground
gets forward and drives to cover
comes forward and drives him down to midwicket
uses his feet and drives him down to long-on
very slow through the air and he pushes it softly to point
comes well forward and drives him down the pitch
wants to drive straight but gets an inside edge to midwicket
Ajmal decides it's time to generous and bowls him a friendly full toss, Hussey moved across and clubbed it across the line and sent the ball sailing over deep midwicket
tucks it away wide of square leg
stays back at the crease and cuts him down to point
tossed up and he gets behind the line to defend
comes forward and pushes it back to the bowler
stays back at the crease and defends with soft hands

Clarke's been given lbw and he is reviewing it, lands quite wide outside off and spins back in sharply and hits the top flap of his pad, umpire Llong gave him out and Clarke asked for it to be reviewed because it was a question of the height, replays showed the ball just clipping the top of leg stump, Llong's decision stands
turn and bounce and he goes back at the crease and cuts him wide of point
flatter delivery and fuller, he clips him down to mid-on

Pakistan have struck with two lbws in quick succession! Hussey looked a bit surprised, he was a long way across his stumps and hence exposed the leg stump and a part of middle, the ball spun back in and hit him low on the pads, umpire Ahsan Raza was convinced, Australia have already used up their review
comes well forward and defends
fuller delivery and he clips it to the on side
gets forward and knocks it towards midwicket
flatter delivery and he punches it with the spin to long-on
quicker delivery and defended in front of the stumps
gets forward and steers it down to point
on middle stump and turned to square leg
stays back and clips it with the turn to long-on
gets forward and gets an inside edge to the pads and rolls to the off side
tossed up slowly and the ball hits his pads outside the line of leg
tossed up outside off and he gets forward and defends
slower through the air and clipped towards midwicket, Misbah dived a bit too late
sharp turn from the rough outside off, Hussey wanted to play at it but the ball completely beat him
how did that miss the off stump? It was the doosra and Hussey left it alone, Kamran was appealing - for what we don't know
goes back and cuts him down to cover
gets well forward and defends
goes back and cuts him down to extra cover
goes right back and clips it with the turn to the on side
gets to the pitch of the ball and drives him to long-on
risks exposing all three stumps to sweep him, paddles it to the leg side
flatter delivery and he clips him down to deep square leg
friendly half volley outside off and driven wide of cover, wide long-off runs across and mops up
steers it wide of point and sets off for a quick single
bowls it flatter and he stays back and whips it down to deep square leg
gives it a lot of air and he drives a low full toss to long-off
drops it softly to the off side and sets off
drilled back to the bowler and he dives and stops it, crowd thought that was a catch
another easy single taken, Hussey drops it just wide of point and takes off
too short and wide and easily slapped down to sweeper cover
bowls a tighter line this time, cramps him for room and he taps it back to the bowler
nearly five overthrows! He drops it in front of point and sets off, there was a bit of hesitation but Bailey was home, the throw was wide and it nearly carried to the point boundary
chopped towards point and a fine diving stop by Umar Akmal
a touch too wide and driven down to sweeper cover
bowls that a bit too short, he rocks back and chops it with the turn to deep cover
too flat and short again,  Bailey played a front foot pull to deep square leg
the singles and twos are flowing, this time he gets back and slices it behind square on the off side
straightens a touch and he shoulders arms
stays back and drills it down the ground to long-on
pitches it up and he drives to cover
and now a boundary, this was short and enough width on it for Bailey to stay back and slice it wide of point, third man had no chance
gets across and pushes it down to mid-off
much better, bowls it straighter and Bailey could only push it to mid-off
simolar delivery, he goes back and punches it to the off side
Tanvir's not doing himself any favours by giving width like this, Bailey cuts but doesn't time it as well, Ajmal has a bit of work to do from third man and he does well to slide near the rope
stays beside the line and chops him down to third man
tossed up outside off and pushed down to long-on
gets forward and drives him down to long-off
stays back and clips it with the turn to square leg
tucked to square leg and they pinch a single
gets forward and drives on the up down to cover
this was a touch shorter and Bailey wanted to cut but ended up getting an outside edge to third man, no slip and Shafiq gave up the chase
good length on middle and leg and driven down to long-on
comes round the wicket and Bailey tries to drive and the ball nearly dribbles back to his stumps
tucks him up for room and he punches it down to long-on
gets an inside edge onto his thighs and the ball rolls to the off side
Hussey chips down the track and ends up drilling it back to Junaid who takes it one handed and nearly flings it back
he picked the gap in the field well, it was dropped short and Hussey swivels and pulls it high over square leg, didn't hit it too hard, used the pace of the ball
tossed up outside off and driven to the off side
turns away and he opens the face and steers it to short third man
slower through the air and clipped with the turn to square leg
risks moving across his stumps to paddle it against the turn, hits his pads but outside the line of the stumps
gets forward and clips it to midwicket
gets forward and drives to long-on
good aggression from Junaid! Hussey was down the track and he drove it firmly down the track, Junaid picked up and nearly flung it back
beats him with a jaffa, lovely line and length, Hussey nearly got an edge to the keeper
comes forward and punches it to the off side
on the pads and he fails to clip it away, that's four dot balls
drops it a bit short and he plays a short arm pull along the ground to deep midwicket
comes round the wicket and tucks him up for room, he chops it to the off side
stays back and he punches it towards long-on
beaten in flight and turn and Kamran whips off the bails, lovely delivery from round the wicket, Bailey drags his back foot back and the third umpire takes a look
outside edge and no slip! This one keeps a bit low and Bailey gets a thin edge that beats the keeper and short third man
tossed up and he gets forward and drives straight to cover
stays back and defends down the track
squares him up with the turn but he manages to block it out
flatter delivery and he tucks it down to square leg
very slow through the air, he waits for it to come to him and chops it down the track
stays back and clips it down to midwicket
tossed up on middle and leg and clipped to mid-on
goes back and clips with the turn to mid-on
flatter delivery and he punches it firmly to cover
soft dismissal! Rehman tossed it up on middle and off and Bailey was looking to chip it to the on side but ended up spooning it back to the bowler
leading edge and it just drops short of cover!
waits for it and steers it down to point to get off the mark
tossed up and driven down to square leg
tossed up on middle and off and drilled down the track
flatter delivery and he stays back and he punches it back to the bowler
floated on the pads and it skids through, hits the pads and rolls to the off side, there was an appeal but that was missing leg
made room to cut but ended up stabbing at it towards mid-off
chips down the track, checks his shot and drives back to the bowler
slower through the air and driven back to the bowler
clipped to midwicket and Misbah is alert to dive and stop it
driven down to sweeper cover and Azhar does really well to give chase and pull it back before the rope
down the track and he gets an outside edge which luckily for Maxwell beats point
down the track and he lofts inside out over cover, well clear of the fielders
down the track and he checks his shot and drills it back to the bowler
quite an extraordinary slog! Tossed up on middle and Maxwell was already forward and he slogged it cleanly over deep square leg, good bat speed there
back to back sixes! He was down the track to the pitch of the ball and he lofted it crisply over wide long-on
make it a hat-trick of sixes! Junaid drags it short and the well-set Hussey is forward and pulls it over deep square leg, lovely follow through
gets forward and pushes it straight to cover
makes room and comes forward and pushes it straight to point
makes room and he gets an outside edge down to third man
attempts a cover drive and he gets an inside edge to square leg
low full toss outside off  and he drives him down to long-off
comes well forward and drills it to the off side
comes forward and drives to the off side
stays back, waits for the turn and cuts to point
Shafiq drops the skier! Ajmal bowls round the wicket and Maxwell doesn't quite pick the doosra, gets a thick top edge on the slog and Shafiq runs forward from deep midwicket and drops it
down the track and he clips it to the on side
goes back and cuts him square on the off side and that's his fifty!
full on the stumps and chipped away down to deep midwicket, it was in the air but fell short
slower ball from round the wicket, he tries to pull that to fine leg but he fails to get it past short fine leg
gives him the charge and gets an outside edge to third man
drags that from the off stump and clips him across the line to the on side
fuller delivery and he drills it down to long-on
that was a slower ball outside off and he bowls that too wide, the batsman was down the track
hammers a low toss down to long-on
chance for a run out! He chopped that towards cover and Hussey was struggling, the throw to Kamran was wide and the keeper himself fumbled
brings out the reverse sweep and he places it to short third man
hits the pads as he goes for a wild slog, struck outside the line of leg stump, Ajmal appeals
chips down the track and he hammers it down to long-on, in the air, and that brings up the 50 stand in just 39 balls
drills it down to long-on again, another couple
toys with the bowler with another reverse sweep, single to point
good slower ball, Hussey made room to thunp that and he was beaten outside off
beaten again! This was quicker and Hussey slogged at thin air and nearly lost his off stump
he saw him chipping down the track and dropped it short, he slashed it straight to Umar Akmal at point
Tanvir bowls a good yorker from round the wicket and Maxwell drills it out and Tanvir wrecks it by overstepping, here we go again
that Free Hit didn't cost Pakistan much, Maxwell was across his stumps and ended up getting an inside edge to his boot, Tanvir forgot it was a free hit and actually appealed
high full toss outside the off stump and he's penalised for height
hammers it down to mid-off for a single
the slower ball, Maxwell moves across his stumps and tries to paddle it away but misses
Ajmal its the timber, tossed up on middle and it was a tired slog from Hussey, swished and missed it completely and the middle stump is pushed back
continues round the wicket, he gets forward and pushes it to the off side

down the track and he clips it off his pads and the ball rolls to the on side, Kamran darts across and picks it up and has a shy at the stumps and the batsman was well short, the throw was wide, Maxwell was off the blocks but sent back
Ajmal has picked up two for the over! Maxwell was down the pitch to hammer it straight but he didn't pick the doosra from round the wicket, missed it completely and an easy stumping for Kamran
defensive shot to the off side, a rarity at this stage of the innings
comes round the wicket and he pulls a short one along the ground to deep square leg
fuller delivery on the pads and he works it down to square leg
nibbles at it outside the off stump, Tanvir gets it to shape away at the last minute
squared him up by one that nipped back in, hit his pads and lobbed to the off side
full on the pads and squirted away down to midwicket
it's yet another no-ball! He's being penalised for bowling too wide of the crease, his front foot was just outside the border line, chipped in the air to deep midwicket, good stop there
the free hit costs Pakistan a boundary! Tanvir bowls a low full toss on the pads and Christian shuffles and clips it wide of short fine leg
goes back and punches him wide of Misbah at cover
teases him with a flatter delivery, he drills it back to the bowler
squared up by turn, nips back and hits the pads and rolls to the on side
keeps him quiet again, no room to free his arms, he punches it back to the bowler
Christian has no clue how to play him, tucks it off his pads to the on side
clips it to square leg and it will just be a single
bowls that full and wide outside off and Christian gets across and hammers it to deep cover for a boundary
chips it down the ground and it drops short and wide of long-on
this was short and he fetched it from outside off and dragged it to deep midwicket, Christian dives and the throw is just wide
squeezes it out to deep midwicket for a single
that was a sharp catch by Jamshed! Christian fetched that from outside off and pulled it flat and fast towards deep midwicket, Jamshed ran across to his right and plucked the ball on the dive
ends his spell with two wickets in as many balls! Junaid bowled that full and straight on the stumps, Johnson had a wild swing and missed it completely, crashed onto off and middle
cut wide of point for a single
leading edge just clears Tanvir who leaps and stretches out his right hand
oh well overthrows! Full outside off and he pushes it straight cover, the fielder has a shy at the stumps but the throw was wide
pushes it down to cover for a single
take that! It was dropped short, Starc swivels and clubs it wide of midwicket and the ball races away, beats the sweeper
and Australia squeeze in four more! Streaky one though, swings and gets an inside edge that sneaks past the stumps and Ajmal at short fine leg

inn2.comm: starts off with a wide and he slides it down the leg side
on a good length outside off and Hafeez stabs at it but times it well enough to beat mid-off, throw  from Christian was a bit wide
continues over the wicket, he stays back at the crease and defends to the off side
another wide down the leg side, Jamshed tried to flick it away
shapes across him and he leaves it alone
drifts on the body and he easily clips it away wide of square leg, the outfield does the rest, nice use of the wrists
lands outside the off stump and he leaves it to the keeper
completely squares him up outside the off stump, he didn't know whether to play or leave it, nipped away and beat him
that was a boundary ball and Maxwell has done brilliantly at short cover to stop a certain four, it was short and wide and slapped away
fullish on the pads and clipped down to midwicket
keeps it nice and straight and he stays back and knocks it back to the bowler
good length outside off and he stays back and clips it to midwicket
good inswinging yorker and Starc appeals for a lbw, Hafeez played all around it but the ball was hitting him outside the line of leg stump
pitches it up but down the leg side and wide called
fetches a full delivery from outside off and clips it in the gap between mid-on and midwicket
bowls it straight on the off stump and he steers it down to point

given lbw immediately and Jamshed is reviewing it, pitched  outside the leg stump, straightened and hit his back leg in front of the stumps, Jamshed consulted Hafeez and it was a good review in the end
fullish on the stumps and he pushes it down to mid-on
low full toss and he pushes it towards cover
stays behind the line and pushes it to the off side
beats him this time, landed it outside off and got it to shape away from the right-hander, good ball
keeps it on a good length outside off and he pushes it to the off side
full outside off and it's an uppish drive down to square third man
that's a terrific shot by Hafeez! It was short of a length and Hafeez read the length very early and clubbed it over midwicket, good bat speed on that one
dropped towards cover and Hafeez did well to call early, good communication
fullish on the pads and clipped down to mid-on

lovely punch off the back foot, it was short and wide and Jamshed played that high on the body and sliced it past the gap between cover and point, Warner gives chase but fails to drag it back properly, the ball hits his boot and rolls back to the rope
nips back in and he gets an inside edge to the pads
takes a quick single to cover, the fielder dives and throws but the batsman was home
inside edge onto the pads as he shapes to defend
stays behind the line and tucks it towards square leg
another forceful shot through the off side, it was short and wide outside the off stump and Jamshed gets on his toes and thumps it past cover and mid-off
gets forward and it's a leading edge towards third man
stays beside the line and steers it to the off side
bowls it straight and he gets behind the line to defend
fullish in length outside off and driven down to mid-off
shot of intent by Jamshed, Johnson bowls it back of a length, Jamshed read the length early, stayed back at the crease and smoked that over mid-on
good length and punched to the off side
slower ball on the stumps and drilled back to the bowler
full and wide outside the off stump and he drags his bat out and jams it to third man
fullish on the pads and clipped straight to midwicket
that was quite wide outside the off stump, didn't offer a shot and I'm surprised that wasn't called a wide
stays beside the line and steers him straight towards cover
that's a good yorker swinging in on the off stump and nicely jammed out to third man
gets across and pushes it down to mid-on
stays behind the line and clips it to the on side
short of a length and Jamshed stands tall and punches it towards mid-on
good length and he stays back and forces it straight to cover
Johnson pitched it up and Jamshed stayed back at the crease and chipped it high and clean over midwicket
bowls it fuller on the pads and he works it away wide of midwicket
fuller ball on the pads and he clips it straight to midwicket
full outside off and he steers it to third man for a single
neat square drive and well fielded by Warner at point, saved another three runs surely
good use of the wrists there, it was too straight on the pads and Hafeez gently flicked it down to fine leg, didn't try and hit it too hard
low full toss outside off and he drives to Johnson at square third man
lovely shot! Full and wide outside off and he leans forward and across and drives forcefully wide of the covers, brings up the fifty stand as well
stays beside the line and steers it towards cover, he is sent back
stays beside the line and he punches it to the off side
keeps just a touch low and he punches it back to the bowler
tucks it softly in front of mid-on and calls early, good running again
slower ball outside off and he softly pushes it towards mid-off
makes a bit of room, gives the charge and biffs it straight to mid-off
full on the stumps and punched back to the bowler
loopy full toss and Hafeez goes right across to the off stump and paddles it down to the leg side
that's a gift down the leg side, tossed that really wide, beats the sweep and the keeper
this one turns and keeps a touch low and beats the edge
once again he errs by sliding it down the leg side, tries to sweep, the ball deflects off Wade
gets forward and drives a full ball down to long-off
gets forward and drives back to the bowler
Hafeez was a touch lucky there, he was down the track to drive straight and gets an outside edge wide of the keeper
full on the stumps and clipped towards deep midwicket

Hafeez has fallen for the trap! There was a fielder at deep square leg and he hit it straight to him, it was short outside off and Hafeez chose to club it across the line, ended up pulling it flat and Mike Hussey did well to catch it on the fall, the wet ball could so easily have slipped out
lands it outside the off stump and he gets across and shoulders arms
stays behind the line and pushes it towards mid-off
low full toss and he clips it across the line wide of midwicket
bowls it on a good length and straight, solidly defended by Azhar
shorter in length and he stays back and clips it towards square leg
bowls it flat from over the wicket and he punches it to the off side
tossed up outside off and he leans forward and drives to sweeper cover
flatter delivery and no turn, he chips it down to midwicket
drops it short and he goes right back at the crease and pulls it down to long-on
tossed up outside off and he drives past sweeper cover
tossed up on middle and clipped to midwicket
lovely delivery, drew him forward and the ball landed on the seam and held its line and beat Azhar
Azhar decides to chip down the track before delivery and a distracted Christian bowled it too wide of the off stump
gets beside the line and steers him down to deep point
keeps it nice and straight and he punches it back to the bowler
Jamshed capitalises on a short ball from Christian, picked the length early, swiveled and pounded it over deep square leg, there was a fielder in the deep but Jamshed cleared him
